{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_35","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `io.fabric8:kubernetes-model-admissionregistration:7.7.0`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-7906-fails-javac-compile-io.fabric8-kubernetes-model-admissionregistration-7.7.0-3eddb8ad\n\nThe original failing stage was `:compileTestJava`: `human-intervention-logs/io.fabric8:kubernetes-model-admissionregistration:7.7.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T04-17-58-215499Z.log` shows 8 `cannot find symbol` errors for removed `withNewMetadata(...)` overloads in `Kubernetes_model_admissionregistrationTest.java`. The preserved candidate commit `198f3ad861da98e71813aebadf8926cc00c52d8f` updates the test to build `ListMeta` explicitly and later reruns pass: `human-intervention-logs/io.fabric8:kubernetes-model-admissionregistration:7.7.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T04-19-50-491035Z.log`, `.../gradle-test-2026-06-06T04-20-42-604089Z.log`, `.../gradle-test-2026-06-06T04-20-58-552928Z.log`, and `.../gradle-test-2026-06-06T04-21-14-415761Z.log` all end with `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` and 9/9 tests passing.\n\nThe workflow still finished as a failure most likely during metrics/stat recording rather than test execution. `stats/io.fabric8/kubernetes-model-admissionregistration/7.7.0/execution-metrics.json` records `\"status\": \"failure\"`, `generated_loc: 0`, `code_coverage_percent: 0.0`, and `\"artifacts\": {\"test_file\":\"None\",\"metadata_file\":\"None\"}`, and there is no corresponding `stats/io.fabric8/kubernetes-model-admissionregistration/7.7.0/stats.json` or dynamic-access report. The other relevant logs are `human-intervention-logs/io.fabric8:kubernetes-model-admissionregistration:7.7.0/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-06-06T04-19-50-479960Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/io.fabric8:kubernetes-model-admissionregistration:7.7.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`.\n\nNext steps:\n- Review or cherry-pick the preserved candidate from commit `198f3ad861da98e71813aebadf8926cc00c52d8f`, especially the `Kubernetes_model_admissionregistrationTest.java` change replacing `withNewMetadata(...)` with `ListMetaBuilder` + `withMetadata(...)`.\n- Re-run the javac-fix/stat generation flow for `io.fabric8:kubernetes-model-admissionregistration:7.7.0` and confirm `stats/io.fabric8/kubernetes-model-admissionregistration/7.7.0/stats.json` and dynamic-access coverage are actually produced.\n- If the rerun still reports failure after tests pass, inspect the metrics-writing path via `forge/.pending_metrics.json` and `stats/io.fabric8/kubernetes-model-admissionregistration/7.7.0/execution-metrics.json`, since the compile/native test lane itself appears fixed."}}
